Love it

Its so refreshing to order Chinese food and be greeted by a smile in this neighborhood. Janet the cashier, was so nice and friendly while I ordered. The egg rolls here are by far the best around, they were fresh, crisp, and you could actually taste the ingredients. They tasted like they were freshly made, unlike the greasy, overcooked, gummy-tasting ones you'll get from other places around here. The dishes are tasty and well-prepared. This is one Chinese food restaurant in this area that actually cares about serving its customers. Hopefully people will appreciate good food and good service and dont abuse the people who work there.
